
/*
 * // This Hyperlambda code demonstrates how to perform a SQL read operation on a SQLite database using the [data.read] slot. 
 * // It specifies the database type as SQLite and targets the "categories" table, selecting the "id", "name", and "description" columns. 
 * // The [where] clause is prepared for additional conditions, using the [and] slot to combine multiple conditions if needed.
 * // 1. [data.read] - Initiates a read operation from the database.
 * // 2. [database-type] - Specifies the type of database being used, in this case, SQLite.
 * // 3. [table] - Indicates the table from which to read data, here it is "categories".
 * // 4. [columns] - Lists the specific columns to be selected from the table.
 * // 5. [where] - Prepares the query for conditional filtering of results.
 * // 6. [and] - Allows for combining multiple conditions within the [where] clause.
 */
data.read
   database-type:sqlite
   table:categories
   columns
      categories.id
      categories.name
      categories.description
   where
      and
